      "role": "user",
      "content": "interesting. you're leaning pretty heavily into that traditional European profile. while that's definitely a core segment, i was wondering about the growth markets. as the brand looks to expand, do you think there's any room for a person of color in this \"ideal\" persona, or does the brand's heritage identity inherently clash with a more diverse demographic? i'm trying to figure out if there's a way to message to a non-white consumer without losing that sense of \"old money\" exclusivity you mentioned.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
